<HEADLINE>
FT  20 SEP 93 / Izetbegovic defiant
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA SILBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BELGRADE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bosnia's President Alija Izetbegovic at the weekend cast doubt over whether
he would endorse a plan for the republic's partition after mediators failed
to win concessions from Serb and Croat leaders, writes Laura Silber in
Belgrade.
'Peace is everybody's dream in Bosnia-Hercegovina, but not peace at any
price,' Mr Izetbegovic said.
Lord Owen and Mr Thorvald Stoltenberg, the international mediators, had
accelerated their efforts to clinch a deal between the three leaders of
Bosnia's rival communities.
But Lord Owen was quoted as saying that, if there was no sign of a
breakthrough, a meeting scheduled for tomorrow might not take place.
