FT  20 SEP 93 / World News in Brief: Demjanjuk free to leave Israel
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Israel's Supreme Court rejected demands for another trial for John
Demjanjuk, 73, acquitted in July of being 'Ivan the Terrible' who
exterminated Jews in Nazi-occupied Poland. It ruled he was free to leave the
country seven years after he was extradited from the US.
