<HEADLINE>
FT  18 SEP 93 / International Company News: David Packard leaves HP chair
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR David Packard, who co-founded Hewlett-Packard in 1939, yesterday
announced his retirement as chairman of the electronics group at the age of
81, writes Martin Dickson. He will be succeeded by Mr Lewis Platt, the
52-year-old president and chief executive, who will retain his existing
titles.
Mr Packard will become a director emeritus of the company, as is his
co-founder, Mr William Hewlett. The two, pioneers in the early life of the
US electronics industry, built HP into what is now the 24th largest
industrial company in the US.
Mr Platt, a 26-year veteran at HP, replaced Mr John Young as chief executive
in July last year.
