<HEADLINE>
FT  18 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Magnolia looks abroad for growth
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Magnolia Group, the picture frame and reproductions company, raised pre-tax
profits from Pounds 52,000 to Pounds 76,000 in the first half of 1993.
Turnover fell from Pounds 9.47m to Pounds 9.05m.
The company said the UK remained quiet but exports showed an improvement of
150 per cent. The result was helped by lower interest charges of Pounds
93,000 (Pounds 108,000). Gearing at the period end was 18 per cent.
Earnings per share were 0.92p (0.61p). The interim dividend is again being
passed.
