<HEADLINE>
FT  18 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Parambe hit by lower art income
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Parambe, which deals in securities and works of art, suffered a fall in
pre-tax profits from Pounds 68,642 to Pounds 40,238 in the first half of
1993.
The result reflected a sharp fall in income from works of art, where Ashlar,
the art dealing offshoot, was unable to replace profits earned in 1991 from
the sales of old master drawings to an American museum. Current sales were
still 'disappointingly slow.'
Net asset value per share rose by 18 per cent to 71.6p in the period, mainly
due to a 33 per cent rise in the value of the investment portfolio.
Security dealing income grew from Pounds 4,140 to Pounds 47,240, while the
art contribution fell to Pounds 18,263 (Pounds 107,627). Investment income
was little changed at Pounds 41,289 (Pounds 40,852).
Earnings per share declined to 0.49p (0.83p), but the interim dividend is
unchanged at 0.55p.
